05747nam a22008535i 9783110724790DE-B159720221107062033.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221107t20222022gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2022941713  a97831107247907 a10.1515/97831107247902doi  a(DE-B1597)571414  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04aThe Theory and Practice of Language Faculty Science /ced. by Hajime Hoji, Yukinori Takubo, Daniel Plesniak. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (XIV, 458 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aThe Mouton-NINJAL Library of Linguistics [MNLL] ,x2626-9201 ;v300tFrontmatter -- tSeries Preface -- tPreface -- tContents -- tPart 1: The Past History of Our Attempts to Detect C-command -- tFrom Compatibility to Testability – Some Historical Background -- tOn Non-individual-denoting So-words -- tResearch Heuristics in Language Faculty Science -- tPart 2: The Correlational Approach -- tThe Key Tenets of Language Faculty Science -- tDetection of C-command Effects -- tReplication: Predicted Correlations of Judgments in Japanese -- tPredicted Correlations of Judgments in English -- tImplementing Experiments on the Language Faculty -- tPart 3: LFS as an Exact Science -- tLanguage Faculty Science and Physics -- tConclusion: Why Language Faculty Science? -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe book demonstrates that it is possible to study the language faculty with the core scientific method, i.e., by deducing definite predictions from hypotheses and obtaining and replicating experimental results precisely in accordance with the predictions.In light of the "reproducibility crisis" as extensively addressed in recent years in a number of fields, the demonstration that rigorous replication can be obtained in the study of the language faculty in terms of correlational and categorical predictions is particularly significant. While the claim has been made over the years that Chomsky’s research program is meant to be a scientific study of the language faculty, a conceptual and methodological articulation has never been made as to how we can accumulate our knowledge about the language faculty by the basic scientific method, including, most crucially, how exactly we can put our hypotheses to rigorous empirical and experimental test.The book proposes how to do that by providing a conceptual basis for the methodology for language faculty science. The book also offers empirical demonstrations of the viability of the proposed methodology. The experiments were conducted with Japanese and English speakers. Overall, the book explores new directions for the study of the mind.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCategorial Prediction.  aExperiments in Linguistics.  aLanguage Faculty Science.  aScientific Methodology.1 aHoji, Hajime, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoji, Hajime, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMukai, Emi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlesniak, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlesniak, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTakubo, Yukinori, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUeyama, Ayumi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook